column2: GRCop alloys are powder metallurgy alloys that can be consolidated by a variety of means including additive

column1: manufacturing. The GRCop-42 and GRCop-84 materials referenced in this section were consolidated by hot
extrusion, also referred to as wrought. To provide the closest comparison of the properties, only these data sets will
be presented here with the exception of the creep data.
